<div id="review_167044390" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/167044390" />
    <a title="Anthony" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5001511-anthony"><img alt="Anthony" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1487488302p2/5001511.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/167044390?book_show_action=true">May 10, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Anthony" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Anthony" href="/user/show/5001511-anthony">Anthony</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5001511-anthony?shelf=reviewed-books">reviewed-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5001511-anthony?shelf=books-i-own">books-i-own</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5001511-anthony?shelf=westerns">westerns</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer167044390" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10718829293760788884">The Haunted Mesa is a book consisting of approximately 250 pages of a man trying to decide when and how to save his friend in another world and less than 100 pages of him actually doing it. Not one of the worst books I&apos;ve ever read, but one that is disappointingly mediocre. Especially given the fact that I had read it as a child and had fond memories of it. I have read all of Louis L&apos;amour&apos;s books, every single one of them between 4th and 6th grade and he was my all time favorite author during t</span>
  <span id="freeText10718829293760788884" style="display:none">The Haunted Mesa is a book consisting of approximately 250 pages of a man trying to decide when and how to save his friend in another world and less than 100 pages of him actually doing it. Not one of the worst books I've ever read, but one that is disappointingly mediocre. Especially given the fact that I had read it as a child and had fond memories of it. I have read all of Louis L'amour's books, every single one of them between 4th and 6th grade and he was my all time favorite author during that time period. As an adult, I plan on re-reading them. Hopefully, the rest of them won't fall as flat on its face as this one did.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10718829293760788884" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


