<div id="review_2677011391" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2677011391" />
    <a title="Sean Cozart" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/52894547-sean-cozart"><img alt="Sean Cozart" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2677011391?book_show_action=true">Jan 16, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sean Cozart" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sean Cozart" href="/user/show/52894547-sean-cozart">Sean Cozart</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2677011391" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15016878664751153547">I have a lot to say about this book because it appears to be not well liked among the fans. This novel is a perfect example of great writing, that an author can be successful in multiple genres. And this book especially is one of many reasons why I believe Louis L&apos;Amour is one of the best authors of all time.<br/><br/>In a normal sense, this isn&apos;t the classic western outlaw, gun-slinging L&apos;Amour type of writing we are use to. However, I see the protagonist of this story, Mike Raglan, as a modern cowboy. H</span>
  <span id="freeText15016878664751153547" style="display:none">I have a lot to say about this book because it appears to be not well liked among the fans. This novel is a perfect example of great writing, that an author can be successful in multiple genres. And this book especially is one of many reasons why I believe Louis L'Amour is one of the best authors of all time.<br /><br />In a normal sense, this isn't the classic western outlaw, gun-slinging L'Amour type of writing we are use to. However, I see the protagonist of this story, Mike Raglan, as a modern cowboy. He is good with a gun, knows how to survive and has his animal companion. Also to add, he acts like a drifter from other Western novels. To wrap that part up, I don't see a huge change from the main format. <br /><br />I absolutely love this book and for many reasons. I really like how the story is very thought-provoking. The beginning of the story is high in suspense due to strange and (to those that read at night) scary phenomena. The story eventually evolves into a science fiction-ish book and provides many questions such as is such a thing possible and if so how? The point is, the author writes to strongly encourage the readers to think. This also leads me to believe he was teaching us a lesson. He makes a thought provoking novel about an ancient society where free speech/thought is prohibited. He theme of the story is to be creative and seek for more knowledge. Don't let your peers and society bring you down to think their way. <br /><br />I highly recommend this book to any potential readers, it is by far one of the fascinating reads I've had in a while. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="15016878664751153547" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


