    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_250313748" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/250313748" />
    <a title="Sandy Weir" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/854856-sandy-weir"><img alt="Sandy Weir" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1344805107p2/854856.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/250313748?book_show_action=true">Dec 22, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sandy Weir" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sandy Weir" href="/user/show/854856-sandy-weir">Sandy Weir</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer250313748" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5030254632690234267">I do not know exactly when this book arrived on my stack to read, but it certainly captivated me with suspense immediately. And it was a book you really should start on Friday night! Reason being that you can hopefully sleep in late after not being able to put it down all night! I had drifted through other L&apos;Amour books and enjoyed them mildly. This one seemed to be unique. <br/>Finding the &quot;Popol Vuh&quot; as a source for some of the information recalled my reading that work as a student in a high school</span>
  <span id="freeText5030254632690234267" style="display:none">I do not know exactly when this book arrived on my stack to read, but it certainly captivated me with suspense immediately. And it was a book you really should start on Friday night! Reason being that you can hopefully sleep in late after not being able to put it down all night! I had drifted through other L'Amour books and enjoyed them mildly. This one seemed to be unique. <br />Finding the "Popol Vuh" as a source for some of the information recalled my reading that work as a student in a high school exchange program to Guatemala. It is the first recorded history of how the Mayan civilization came to this world. Other Asian references of similar history or mythology were also given in the text.<br /><br />So in summary, I think this book drifts away from the author's traditional westerns and begins to take elements of fantasy or science fiction (while still dressed in the geography and culture of the south-west).<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="5030254632690234267" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


