<div id="review_265290253" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/265290253" />
    <a title="Dale" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4696608-dale"><img alt="Dale" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1293139243p2/4696608.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/265290253?book_show_action=true">Jan 20, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dale" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dale" href="/user/show/4696608-dale">Dale</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer265290253" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13909041941555068486"><b>This sci-fi book by Louis L&apos;Amour could have been so much more.</b><br/><br/>Yes, that&apos;s right. Louis L&apos;Amour, author of more than 100 westerns wrote a sci-fi book. It is set in familiar territory for him, the American Southwest and it concerns the disappearance of the Anasazi Indians more than 600 years ago. If you are unfamiliar with the Anasazi, they are the builders of the adobe brick cliff dwellings that are scattered across the Southwestern desert. Their most famous site is at Mesa Verde National Monume</span>
  <span id="freeText13909041941555068486" style="display:none"><b>This sci-fi book by Louis L'Amour could have been so much more.</b><br /><br />Yes, that's right. Louis L'Amour, author of more than 100 westerns wrote a sci-fi book. It is set in familiar territory for him, the American Southwest and it concerns the disappearance of the Anasazi Indians more than 600 years ago. If you are unfamiliar with the Anasazi, they are the builders of the adobe brick cliff dwellings that are scattered across the Southwestern desert. Their most famous site is at Mesa Verde National Monument.<br /><br />The premise of the book is that the Anasazi were able to travel back and forth to another dimension, the third world mentioned in Hopi and Mayan legends. <br /><br />Read more at <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://dwdsreviews.blogspot.com/2012/01/haunted-mesa-by-louis-lamour.html">http://dwdsreviews.blogspot.com/2012/...</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="13909041941555068486" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


