<div id="review_937661752" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/937661752" />
    <a title="Jordan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/30121457-jordan"><img alt="Jordan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1397621498p2/30121457.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/937661752?book_show_action=true">May 14, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jordan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jordan" href="/user/show/30121457-jordan">Jordan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30121457-jordan?shelf=a-league-of-it-s-own">a-league-of-it-s-own</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30121457-jordan?shelf=books-i-take-camping">books-i-take-camping</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer937661752" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14327164362590838830">This is a book that I absolutely love. <br/><br/>It&apos;s classic L&apos;Amour. Beautiful scenery and a suspenseful story that takes your breath away.<br/><br/>However, there&apos;s a twist to the usual L&apos;Amour equation of greatness.<br/><br/>And that twist is the thing I love about this book. <br/><br/>Because as crazy as it is, it&apos;s L&apos;Amour writing it and you know to trust him. He is that grandfather-storyteller we all have had who can tell us the wildest story but make it believable. It&apos;s a fish tale in the middle of the desert. <br/><br/>So read it...<br/><br/>Be </span>
  <span id="freeText14327164362590838830" style="display:none">This is a book that I absolutely love. <br /><br />It's classic L'Amour. Beautiful scenery and a suspenseful story that takes your breath away.<br /><br />However, there's a twist to the usual L'Amour equation of greatness.<br /><br />And that twist is the thing I love about this book. <br /><br />Because as crazy as it is, it's L'Amour writing it and you know to trust him. He is that grandfather-storyteller we all have had who can tell us the wildest story but make it believable. It's a fish tale in the middle of the desert. <br /><br />So read it...<br /><br />Be transported away...<br /><br />Welcome to the Mesas.<br /><br /><br /><br />Recommendation for those that liked Haunted Mesa. I thought Thunderhead by Douglas Preston and Lincoln Child was a great spiritual successor to this novel. <br /><br />5/5</span>
